# Operation Batches on /bytes

Operation batches are stored on Swarm `/bytes`, not in a feed. They are immutable and content-addressed — the batch reference IS the hash of its encrypted contents.

## Why not feeds

Feeds are mutable pointers. Operation data must never change once written, so batches go directly to `/bytes`. The document manifest feed holds the list of batch references in order.

## Schema (decrypted)

```json
[
  {
    "id": "op-aaa",
    "index": 0,
    "skip": 0,
    "timestampUtcMs": "1712750460000",
    "hash": "abc123...",
    "action": {
      "id": "act-001",
      "type": "CREATE_BUDGET",
      "input": { "name": "Q1 Budget", "year": 2026 },
      "scope": "global",
      "context": {
        "signer": {
          "user": { "address": "0xAlice", "networkId": "1" },
          "app": { "name": "connect", "key": "..." }
        }
      }
    }
  }
]
```

## Fields

- `index`: position in the operation log for the scope
- `skip`: number of operations reshuffled past during conflict resolution
- `hash`: integrity check on the operation
- `action.context.signer`: identifies who signed the operation
